{"author":{"id":"93eb9dc474bb6ead415a968b3de0f30bab909202028955ad49f28cd00394d9ef"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1714922742,"nonce":"D5Cw2jK+YXz+ROPJbPkPDmYakbc=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOJl1IZM583OH0","github-url":"https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/issues/28#issuecomment-2094850548"},"message":"Due to this issue I stopped using Aerospace (and Mac altogether) for some time. However, I need to swtich to MacOS temporarily and having used i3 for quite some time I decided to figure out the solution. I saw the skhd workaround, but since I am using karabiner with [goku](https://github.com/yqrashawn/GokuRakuJoudo) for my keyboard shortcuts, I will paste my version of the workaround.\n\n`karabiner.edn`\n```\n:main [\n     {:des \"Change left_option to 3 modifiers combination, f17 when used alone\"\n         :rules [[:left_option :!COleft_control nil {:alone [:f17]}]]}\n  ]\n```\n\nthis remaps left option to alt-cmd-ctrl, which can then be used in Aerospace shortcuts, leaving right option as the default modifier for accented letters. I also had to modify other shortcuts from alt to alt-cmd-ctrl but the sample below should be enough to get started.\n\n`.aerospace.toml`\n```\nalt-cmd-ctrl-1 = 'workspace 1'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-2 = 'workspace 2'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-3 = 'workspace 3'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-4 = 'workspace 4'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-5 = 'workspace 5'\n\n\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-1 = 'move-node-to-workspace 1'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-2 = 'move-node-to-workspace 2'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-3 = 'move-node-to-workspace 3'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-4 = 'move-node-to-workspace 4'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-5 = 'move-node-to-workspace 5'\n\n```\n\nI _think_ karabiner does not need Secure Input to be disabled. It would be awesome if Aerospace could differentiate between left and right modifier keys by itself so perhaps this issue should be left open for reference. But the workaround works well enough that my original problem is resolved.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1714923029,"nonce":"K7FdQF5RWJjmRXXt54uP+3V+LRc=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOJl1IZM583OH0zkWeudU"},"target":"714fb499d8bab0ca7a209c75624ff8702bd3319a44259710e804060e99862666","message":"Due to this issue I stopped using Aerospace (and Mac altogether) for some time. However, I need to swtich to MacOS temporarily and having used i3 for quite some time I decided to figure out the solution. I saw the skhd workaround, though I was under the impression that Aerospace was intercepting the option key completely. I haven't checked the code if anything changed in that area but now I got this to work (with a workaround) and since I am using karabiner with [goku](https://github.com/yqrashawn/GokuRakuJoudo) for my keyboard shortcuts, I will paste my version of the workaround.\n\n`karabiner.edn`\n```\n:main [\n     {:des \"Change left_option to 3 modifiers combination, f17 when used alone\"\n         :rules [[:left_option :!COleft_control nil {:alone [:f17]}]]}\n  ]\n```\n\nthis remaps left option to alt-cmd-ctrl, which can then be used in Aerospace shortcuts, leaving right option as the default modifier for accented letters. I also had to modify other shortcuts from alt to alt-cmd-ctrl but the sample below should be enough to get started.\n\n`.aerospace.toml`\n```\nalt-cmd-ctrl-1 = 'workspace 1'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-2 = 'workspace 2'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-3 = 'workspace 3'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-4 = 'workspace 4'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-5 = 'workspace 5'\n\n\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-1 = 'move-node-to-workspace 1'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-2 = 'move-node-to-workspace 2'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-3 = 'move-node-to-workspace 3'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-4 = 'move-node-to-workspace 4'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-5 = 'move-node-to-workspace 5'\n\n```\n\nI _think_ karabiner does not need Secure Input to be disabled. It would be awesome if Aerospace could differentiate between left and right modifier keys by itself so perhaps this issue should be left open for reference. But the workaround works well enough that my original problem is resolved.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1714923093,"nonce":"gRvyj+62P/l2kY/IIqVVxNekKEk=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOJl1IZM583OH0zkWeusk"},"target":"714fb499d8bab0ca7a209c75624ff8702bd3319a44259710e804060e99862666","message":"Due to this issue I stopped using Aerospace (and Mac altogether) for some time. However, I need to swtich to MacOS temporarily and having used i3 for quite some time I decided to figure out the solution. I saw the skhd workaround, though I was under the impression that Aerospace was intercepting the option key completely in that version. I haven't checked the code if anything changed in that area but in the latest version I got this to work (with a workaround) and since I am using karabiner with [goku](https://github.com/yqrashawn/GokuRakuJoudo) for my keyboard shortcuts, I will paste my version of the workaround.\n\n`karabiner.edn`\n```\n:main [\n     {:des \"Change left_option to 3 modifiers combination, f17 when used alone\"\n         :rules [[:left_option :!COleft_control nil {:alone [:f17]}]]}\n  ]\n```\n\nthis remaps left option to alt-cmd-ctrl, which can then be used in Aerospace shortcuts, leaving right option as the default modifier for accented letters. I also had to modify other shortcuts from alt to alt-cmd-ctrl but the sample below should be enough to get started.\n\n`.aerospace.toml`\n```\nalt-cmd-ctrl-1 = 'workspace 1'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-2 = 'workspace 2'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-3 = 'workspace 3'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-4 = 'workspace 4'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-5 = 'workspace 5'\n\n\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-1 = 'move-node-to-workspace 1'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-2 = 'move-node-to-workspace 2'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-3 = 'move-node-to-workspace 3'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-4 = 'move-node-to-workspace 4'\nalt-cmd-ctrl-shift-5 = 'move-node-to-workspace 5'\n\n```\n\nI _think_ karabiner does not need Secure Input to be disabled. It would be awesome if Aerospace could differentiate between left and right modifier keys by itself so perhaps this issue should be left open for reference. But the workaround works well enough that my original problem is resolved.","files":null}]}